{"type":"message","id":"b120934a","parentId":"be5927ca","timestamp":"2026-04-30T15:49:42.962Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby wants a clear breakdown of what's done vs what's left. Let me check the section files to give an accurate status.","thinkingSignature":"5812fbf88168ba866b01561001a5cb4c96197719b62d5ddb910956e3cc47898c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2n1rmw74o8rp_1","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":20,"path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/Section-7-Your-First-Automation.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2n1rmw74o8rp_2","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":20,"path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/Section-8-Real-World-Workflows.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2n1rmw74o8rp_3","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":20,"path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/Section-9-Advanced-Techniques.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2n1rmw74o8rp_4","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":20,"path":"/Users/bobbygalletta/Desktop/OpenClaw/OpenClaw-Guide-By-Bobby/Section-10-Money-Making-Use-Cases.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":40414,"output":267,"cacheRead":224,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":40905,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777564177688,"responseId":"0642ad11fcb74d14d55f1e9edd758bfa"}}
{"type":"message","id":"c9fc387e","parentId":"b120934a","timestamp":"2026-04-30T15:49:43.222Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2n1rmw74o8rp_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# OpenClaw Guide by Bobby G.\n\n*A practical, real-world guide to OpenClaw — written by someone who uses it daily.*\n\n---\n\n## Section 7: Your First Automation — The Morning Brief Skill\n\nThis is where it gets real. I'm going to show you how to build and install your first automation — the **Morning Brief skill**. This is the one I use every single day to start my morning right. I wake up, and before I'm even out of bed, everything I need to know is already there.\n\nOnce you see how powerful this is — something that runs automatically, every day, without you doing anything — you'll start seeing all kinds of other things you can build.\n\n---\n\n### What Does the Morning Brief Actually Do?\n\nEvery morning at 5:30 AM, my OpenClaw sends me a full briefing via Telegram. It includes:\n\n- **Today's weather** — current temperature, what it feels like, the high and low, wind, humidity, UV index, rain chance. Plus an hour-by-hour breakdown so I know what to wear and when to go outside.\n- **A Bible verse with personal motivation** — something relevant to what's on my calendar or what's coming up in my life that day. Not just a random verse — one that actually speaks to my situation.\n\n[159 more lines in file. Use offset=21 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1777564183222}}
{"type":"message","id":"a98a7312","parentId":"c9fc387e","timestamp":"2026-04-30T15:49:43.223Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2n1rmw74o8rp_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# OpenClaw Guide by Bobby G.\n\n*A practical, real-world guide to OpenClaw — written by someone who uses it daily.*\n\n---\n\n## Section 8: Real-World Workflows — Content Creation, Brand Building & YouTube\n\nThis is where we get into what OpenClaw can actually DO for you in your daily life. I'm going to walk through real workflows that you can set up and start using today — workflows for creating content, building your personal brand, and running a YouTube operation.\n\nThese aren't hypothetical use cases. These are things people are doing right now with OpenClaw, and I'm going to show you exactly how they work.\n\n---\n\n### How OpenClaw Fits Into Your Creative Workflow\n\nThe traditional way to create content goes something like this:\n\n1. You sit down to work\n2. You spend 20 minutes getting inspired\n\n[238 more lines in file. Use offset=21 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1777564183222}}
{"type":"message","id":"1e77cc02","parentId":"a98a7312","timestamp":"2026-04-30T15:49:43.223Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2n1rmw74o8rp_3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# OpenClaw Guide by Bobby G.\n\n*A practical, real-world guide to OpenClaw — written by someone who uses it daily.*\n\n---\n\n## Section 9: Advanced Techniques — Reverse Prompting, Multi-Agent Setups & Proactive Automation\n\nBy now you've got the fundamentals down. You know what OpenClaw is, how to set it up, and how to use it for real workflows. This section is where we go deeper — the techniques that separate people who use OpenClaw from people who get transform by it.\n\nThese aren't complicated, but they're not obvious. Most people never discover them because they never push past the basics. If you're ready to really unlock what OpenClaw can do, keep reading.\n\n---\n\n### Technique 1: Reverse Prompting — Let OpenClaw Lead\n\nMost people prompt like this:\n> \"Build me a task tracker\"\n\nThat's forward prompting. You tell OpenClaw what to do, it does it. That's fine, but it limits you to what you can think to ask.\n\n[237 more lines in file. Use offset=21 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1777564183222}}
{"type":"message","id":"a07e3c24","parentId":"1e77cc02","timestamp":"2026-04-30T15:49:43.223Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2n1rmw74o8rp_4","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# OpenClaw Guide by Bobby G.\n\n*A practical, real-world guide to OpenClaw — written by someone who uses it daily.*\n\n---\n\n## Section 10: Money-Making Use Cases with OpenClaw\n\nThis is the section most people are waiting for. You've learned what OpenClaw is, how to set it up, how to use it for content and brand building, and advanced techniques. Now let's talk about how to actually make money with it.\n\nOpenClaw isn't just a productivity tool — it's a business builder. People are using it to create income streams, automate client work, build products, and scale businesses. This section covers the real ways to turn OpenClaw into a revenue generator.\n\nThe key principle underneath all of this: **OpenClaw makes you a force multiplier.** It lets one person do what previously required a team. That asymmetry — your skills plus AI amplification — is where the money is.\n\n---\n\n### Use Case 1: Sell Your OpenClaw Expertise\n\nThis is the most direct path to income using what you've learned in this guide. You're already building expertise — why not package it and sell it?\n\n\n[234 more lines in file. Use offset=21 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1777564183223}}
